### Address Validation API Documentation
### POST /api/v1/validate-address
### Validates a US address using SmartyStreets provider with Redis caching
###
### Headers:
### Content-Type: application/json
###
### Body:
### {
###   "address": "string"
### }
###
### Response Status Codes:
### 200 - Success (valid, corrected, or unverifiable)
### 400 - Bad Request (invalid input)
### 429 - Too Many Requests (rate limited)
### 500 - Internal Server Error
### 503 - Service Unavailable (provider/circuit breaker issues)
###
### Success Response Format:
### {
###   "status": "valid" | "corrected" | "unverifiable",
###   "inputAddress": "string",
###   "standardizedAddress": "string", // only for valid/corrected
###   "originalInput": "string",       // only for corrected
###   "details": {                     // only for valid/corrected
###     "streetNumber": "string",
###     "streetName": "string",
###     "streetSuffix": "string",
###     "secondaryDesignator": "string", // optional
###     "secondaryNumber": "string",     // optional
###     "city": "string",
###     "state": "string",
###     "zipCode": "string",
###     "zipPlus4": "string"
###   },
###   "error": "string" // only for unverifiable
### }

### Example: Valid Address
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/validate-address
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "address": "123 Main St, Springfield, IL 62701"
}

### Example: Corrected Address
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/validate-address
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "address": "123 main street springfield illinois 62701"
}

### Example: Unverifiable Address
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/validate-address
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "address": "123 Fake Street, Nonexistent City, XX 00000"
}

